6000|$|Most mothers {{would have}} taken hold of the <b>matrimonial</b> <b>matter</b> in the old {{regulation}} way; they {{would have given the}} girls a talking to, of a solemn sort and untactful--a lecture calculated to defeat its own purpose, by producing tears and secret rebellion; and the said mothers would have further damaged the business by requesting the young mechanics to discontinue their attentions. But this mother was different. She was practical. She said nothing to any of the young people concerned, nor to any one else except Sally. He listened to her and understood; understood and admired. He said: ...|$|R
