50|$|The {{original}} Brussels II regulation was Regulation (EC) No 1347/2000. It {{was replaced}} with Council Regulation (EC) No 2201/2003 concerning jurisdiction and the recognition and enforcement of judgments which came into force on 1 August 2004 and applies from 1 March 2005 in <b>matrimonial</b> <b>matters</b> and the matters of parental responsibility. The revised Brussels II legislation is variously referred to as Brussels II bis or B, or Brussels IIA, or the new Brussels II and repeals the older regulation.|$|E
